|Comments=The Persian term "davari" is to officiate (particularly in the context of sports) and judge (not in the case of courts/judicial settings, but in the sense of making a ruling in a small conflict or disagreement or evaluating  a situation or forming an opinion on something, these instances constitute the context in which "davari" is used. All the same the closest corresponding English frame is "judicial action."
